      "message": "[Critical] Line 83: This still has a lost-event race: `authStateSubject` is a `PublishSubject`, so any auth callback emitted by `addDevice()` before this subscription is installed is dropped permanently. The previous code had the opposite race with `operationId`, but moving the subscription after the call does not make the flow safe. Subscribe first and defer filtering by operation id until it has been assigned, or use a replay/buffered per-operation stream from `AccountsService`.\n```suggestion\nvar expectedOperationId: UInt32?\n\nlet disposable \u003d self.accountService.authStateSubject\n    .filter { [weak self] authResult in\n        guard let self \u003d self,\n              let operationId \u003d expectedOperationId else { return false }\n        return authResult.accountId \u003d\u003d self.account.id \u0026\u0026\n            authResult.operationId \u003d\u003d operationId\n    }\n    .observe(on: MainScheduler.instance)\n    .subscribe(onNext: { [weak self] authResult in\n        self?.handleAuthResult(authResult)\n    })\n\ndisposable.disposed(by: disposeBag)\nexpectedOperationId \u003d self.accountService.addDevice(accountId: account.id, token: jamiAuthentication)\n```",
